7e739706-629d-40d4-93a0-c32c683f7437	caa75853-e702-45db-baad-6cef9d2b38c6	3	LLM_EXTRACTION	{"source_path": "reference/test_emails/FW_ Attached is your invoice #2857 from Alliance Landscape Co LLC.msg", "rendered_prompt": "You are the local LLM extractor for the AP Automation system.\\nReturn only one JSON object. Do not include Markdown, prose, or code fences.\\nExtract facts for the extraction.v1 schema below. The deterministic rules engine will make final routing decisions.\\nDo not invent property codes, destinations, email recipients, or invoice facts. Use null for absent facts.\\nSet confidence below 0.90 when required invoice, property, or business-unit facts are incomplete or uncertain.\\nUse document flags for high-risk conditions such as link_only_invoice, missing_invoice_attachment, past_due, ach_or_auto_draft, ben_e_keith, conflicting_signals, or low_text_quality.\\nAllowed document_type values: invoice, statement, account_summary, contract, pay_application, vendor_question, payment_inquiry, past_due_notice, ach_notice, auto_draft_notice, ben_e_keith_notice, lien_release, unknown.\\nThe JSON object must match this top-level shape exactly: schema_version, extractor, email, document, invoice, business_signals, confidence, evidence.\\nSet extractor.type to \\"codex_cli\\", extractor.name to \\"codex_exec\\", extractor.model to null unless known, and extractor.prompt_version to \\"local_msg_extraction.v1\\".\\n\\nInput email and attachment metadata:\\n{\\n  \\"attachments\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\"content_type\\": null,\\n      \\"file_name\\": \\"Invoic~1.pdf\\",\\n      \\"file_size_bytes\\": 101608,\\n      \\"sha256\\": \\"042d8130c3e2a3ca90c4b5bf9ce4ba58669b91eba02e5e398301d56d71203b3b\\",\\n      \\"storage_path\\": \\"local/attachments/8c03adea-36f1-48c7-b699-cca4c6d70b17/001-Invoic_1.pdf\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\"content_type\\": \\"image/png\\",\\n      \\"file_name\\": \\"image001.png\\",\\n      \\"file_size_bytes\\": 8324,\\n      \\"sha256\\": \\"666bbd84668ae9d10da3d1a8d3b60351acb22b6b02ba8ef26cbb8092ae37c8a2\\",\\n      \\"storage_path\\": \\"local/attachments/8c03adea-36f1-48c7-b699-cca4c6d70b17/002-image001.png\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\"email\\": {\\n    \\"body_text\\": \\"Attached is an example of an invoice received for a property that is 3rd Party Managed by Hillwood and processed via a different payables software system than Medius.  The property address is reviewed and sent to the designated associate who manages payables for that specific building. \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nI have a spreadsheet that details Hillwood owned buildings, 3rd Party managed buildings, and their associated addresses, that is referenced, as the AP Inbox is worked through.  I can send you a copy of this for refence as well.   I imagine the AI feature will need this to learn address specifics?\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nThis invoice would be forwarded to Michele.Fellers@hillwood.com <mailto:Michele.Fellers@hillwood.com>  for processing.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nLeslie Rodriguez\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nAccounts Payable Coordinator \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nHillwood, A Perot Company\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nDirect: 817.224.6343 | Leslie.Rodriguez@Hillwood.com <mailto:Leslie.Rodriguez@Hillwood.com> \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nFrom: Miner, Casey <casey.miner@hillwood.com> \\\\r\\\\nSent: Wednesday, March 4, 2026 4:45 PM\\\\r\\\\nTo: PropertiesAP <Propertiesap@hillwood.com>\\\\r\\\\nCc: Topasna, Denise <denise.topasna@hillwood.com>; Vilbig, Megan <megan.vilbig@hillwood.com>\\\\r\\\\nSubject: Attached is your invoice #2857 from Alliance Landscape Co LLC\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nAttached is Invoice #2857 for work completed at Gateway 51.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nIf you have any questions, please do not hesitate to reach out. \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nThank you and have a wonderful day!\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nCasey Miner\\\\r\\\\